The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 The State Bank of India will hold a property fair SBI Home Loan Mahotsav from October 28 to 30 in the city. The bank will provide concessional rate of interest for loans above five years and up to 20 years. It will also provide concession on processing fees. The bank will also reduce margin requirement on the project cost for home loans. The bank will issue spot-in-principle sanctions based on income and residence proof. 

 IFGL Refractories Ltd has paid Rs 2.35 crore as second instalment of advance income tax for 2007-08. The first instalment of Rs 1.35 crore was paid in June. IFGL manufactures specialised refractories and operating systems for the steel industry.

 Simplex Infrastructures Ltd has bagged orders worth Rs 802 crore in four segments industrial structures, urban utilities, piling and marine structures both in India and abroad. The companys order book stands at Rs 7,000 crore.

 Garden Reach Shipbuilders and Engineers Ltd has a paid dividend of Rs 14.76 crore for 2006-07 on September 24. This is in addition to an interim dividend of Rs 10 crore paid on February 20. The company has posted an 83.9 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 120.14 crore against Rs 65.33 crore a year ago.

 Exim Bank has extended credit worth $100 million to the Nepal government to finance road and rural electrification projects.

 Tata Consultancy Services has helped Bahrains Labour Market Regulatory Authority streamline processes and create an efficient labour market. 

 Mecon ltd has rebuilt Bokaro Steel plants 5-metre tall coke oven battery no. 5. The battery has been rebuilt on an EPC basis. The managing director of the Bokaro Steel plant commissioned the battery on September 16. 

